Premium Job - Senior Project Manager Network Delivery - Communications Project
30 Apr 2014 10:14 PM - UAE
Job Description:
The position is to lead regional network delivery teams , ensuring that delivered projects meet the requirements of both the Saudi Government Customer and UK Government Customer. He will be fully accountable for the effective planning and management of allocated resources to ensure the company annual orders and sales targets.
A permanent role the successful candidate must be a UK citizen and will; -Hold a Batchelor Degree or equivalent in an engineering or other appropriate discipline -Association of Project Managers Professional Qualification (APMP)or similar -Significant experience in telecommunications services industry -Experience in delivering projects utilising ITSM -Proven track record of delivering successful IT based and other forms of communications capability bids. -Sound understanding of bid management and commercial practice -Expert customer relations manager -Sound knowledge of managing budgets -High standard of written and spoken English He may also hold; -ITIL intermediate level qualification or similar -Post Grad qualification such as MBA or MSc
-Business /acquisition experience in UK Defence sector -Experience of the Middle East He will enjoy; -Competitive Tax free salary and company bonus scheme -Fee accommodation with accompanied status -Free healthcare
-Car -Education package (UK) for up to 2 children -Generous leave entitlement
